modules.description: Stores and exposes version metadata including the version string, commit hash, and commit date. Works with string and option types to represent optional build-time information. Useful for embedding version details in binaries or reporting system diagnostics.

Handles in-memory modifications of file content by replacing specific line ranges and supports committing changes to disk with options to apply, fake, or diff the patch. Works directly with file paths, line numbers, and string content. Useful for automated code patching, generating diffs with optional exclusions, or applying transformations to source files during builds or migrations.
